# Asset Management

- Store all images, audio, and other assets in the `assets/` directory.
- Organize assets by type (e.g., `Tiles/`, `Sprites/`, `Audio/`) or feature.
- Do not edit `.import` files directly; these are managed by Godot.
- Use lossless formats (PNG, WAV) for source assets when possible.
- Optimize asset sizes for performance, especially for web or mobile builds.
- Reference assets in scenes/scripts using `res://assets/...` paths.
- Remove unused assets to keep the project clean.
- Keep asset names descriptive and consistent.
- Avoid spaces and special characters in asset filenames.
- Use Godot's import settings for compression and resolution as needed.

## Example
```
assets/
  Tiles/
    All.png
    All.png.import
  Audio/
    jump.wav
    jump.wav.import
```
